text.tspan: An anaesthetist compared the effects of acupuncture and codeine on post-operative
It is almost certain that mean pain relief is different for the different
treatments. There is also extremely strong evidence that mean pain relief
score varies for different blocks (initial assessment of pain tolerance).
dental pain. 32 subjects were grouped into blocks of 4 according to an initial assessment
of pain tolerance. In a blind experiment, the 4 treatment combinations of (codeine/sugar
pill) and (active/inactive acupuncture points) were randomly allocated in each block.
The response was a pain relief score 2 hours after treatment.
